from a terrifying murder rate to appalling 
infant mortality sharon pratt dixon will confront problems that 
would daunt the nations savviest public official when she becomes 
mayor of the nations capital 
but the woman who takes office jan 2 is the very opposite of 
an experienced government bureaucrat and her response to the 
challenges will set the tone for life in a city anxious for an end 
to turbulence after outgoing mayor marion barrys highly publicized 
drug and legal difficulties 
dixon 46 and a former utility company executive swept to 
victory in november in her firstever political campaign she had 
been the first candidate to call on barry to give up his job and 
campaigned on a pledge to root out waste and corruption in city 
government 
last month a blueribbon panel that examined the citys 
deteriorating financial situation recommended that 6000 government 
jobs be eliminated 
so far she isnt saying how shell proceed when she becomes the 
capital citys first woman mayor 
she wont have long to get going on that problem or any other 
the police force continues to grow toward a record level of 
5100 officers yet a record 471 people have been murdered this 
year many of them the result of the citys notorious drug trade 
homelessness public school difficulties chronic prison crowding 
an infant mortality rate higher than many third world countries 
these will be dixons to deal with as well 
solving these dilemmas will take money and the nations capital 
city is broke this years deficit of 100 million could double in 
the next fiscal year 
amidst the gloom are some signs of hope 
the departure of barry who is appealing his cocaine possession 
conviction and sixmonth prison sentence should mean a new spirit 
of goodwill among the city the congress and the bush 
administration 
the annual payment made to the city in lieu of taxes lost on 
federallyowned property has been frozen at 4305 million for five 
years in a visible symbol of congressional dissatisfaction with 
barry 
after a meeting with dixon last month house speaker thomas 
foley said the payment may soon be increased earlier this month 
transportation secretary samuel skinner praised dixon while 
awarding the city 19 million in federal highway funds barry was 
nowhere to be seen 
dixons nofrills style differs sharply from that of barry who 
made no secret of his love for limousines police escorts and other 
trappings of power 
last month the mayorelect said she would all but eliminate the 
24member roundtheclock police security detail that accompanied 
barry to all his official and private functions thats just not 
my style im not comfortable with it dixon said 
ms dixon divorced and the mother of two grown daughters has 
had a career as an electric company executive she also has served 
two terms as treasurer of the democratic national committee 
but her profile in national democratic politics aside she has 
scant experience in local government affairs 
the longawaited study of the citys bureaucracy gives dixon 
who has promised to pare 2000 workers from the city payroll even 
greater momentum to make broad cuts in the 48000 member district 
work force 
it certainly underscores the need to clean out some of the 
midlevel bloat dixon says the need for streamlining for 
better accountability it is all there 
eliminating police jobs could prove unpopular on capitol hill 
where lawmakers critical of city anticrime efforts are nonetheless 
anxious to see dixon take over from barry 
other pressing problems have so far defied solution among them 
the citys 1989 infant mortality rate of 231 per 1000 live births 
was higher than the rate in malaysia mauritius and uruguay 
and even before dixon can take office the sniping has begun 
dixon promises to hit the ground running but so far has 
failed to name any key lieutenants current and former city 
officials assisting her transition are complaining that the passage 
is marked by a lack of direction from dixon herself and her failure 
to list any top priorities for her new administration 
to make matters worse dixon is already dealing with government 
infighting city council chairman john wilson has made no secret of 
his desire to wield more power an advisory group he assembled to 
help him restructure his new job resembles in the words of wamufm 
political commentator mark plotkin a 1994 mayoral exploratory 
committee 
