deputy spokesman richard boucher said the united states merely 
wants china to live up to internationally accepted human rights 
standards 
the harsh tone f the editorial contrasted sharply with the 
generally friendly reception given in beijing last week to richard 
schifter the assistant secretary for human rights 
boucher said needless to say we disagee with its the 
peoples dailys assessment of our human rights policy we 
dont seek to undermine the chinese government nor to interfere in 
its internal affairs 
rather he said the united states tries to point out to chinese 
authorities where they violate international human rights standards 
and to advise china of the likely consequences in terms of us 
policy 
boucher said the united states tries to persuade the chinese 
government to modify its practices to conform to international 
law 
