gangplank shortly after the ship docked off bahrain the pentagon 
leased the ship for six months as a floating hotel for the troops 
at a cost of 31 million 
in a tent in the middle of the desert two young navy hospital 
corpsmen who sing under the name fried brains sang christmas carols 
for the marine combat service support detachment 111 the songs 
included silver bells winter wonderland and in apparent 
violation of rules against singing religious songs in public 
silent night 
in the saudi capital riyadh bob hope performed in a us 
military compound keeping a tradition of entertaining us troops 
at christmas that dates to 1941 for him but the 87yearold 
comedian left marie osmond and the pointer sisters part of his 
show in bahrain again not to offend the saudis with women 
entertainers 
hopes travel itinerary was not disclosed for security reasons 
