young pianist falls in love with his 
beautiful world famous instructor is the oneline synopsis of 
matters of the heart a madeforcable movie premiering tonight 
on the usa network 
its accurate but not true as they say and does a disservice 
to an unabashed romance that stars jane seymour who seems only to 
grow more beautiful as she matures and lends new grace to the term 
middleaged 
shes the soul of this movie in her role as worldclass pianist 
hadley norman a lonely troubled woman who seeks to compose and 
drink in seclusion in a gritty little upstate new york town 
seymour shows courage as an actress in her first scenes 
allowing herself to be photographed looking like an unmade bed 
