the other half of the romance is steven harper chris gartin a 
gifted young pianist stranded in his hometown because he cant 
afford music school he looks ahead and sees only an eternity of 
work in his fathers hardware store 
we spend most of the movies early scenes with steven whos at 
loggerheads with his father excellently acted by james stacy an 
embittered man who lost an arm and leg in vietnam 
instead of encouraging his sons passionate musical ambitions 
the father is hostile to them gartin never overplays his 
18yearold characters angst and frustration its a much more 
powerful performance because of that control 
when steven approaches her for an autograph her wretched 
appearance and harsh neurotic behavior are offputting his 
worship of her artistic ability changes into concern for her as a 
person 
as steven tries to break down the barriers between them showing 
her his passion for the music so too does hadley lower her guard 
finally she consents to teach him and he flourishes 
the dynamics of their relationship begin to evolve his growing 
confidence and musicianship let him see her as a woman and her see 
him as a man a rising glissando of sexual tension turns into a 
emotional and physical involvement 
note there is some of what is charmingly called partial 
nudity but its nothing you wouldnt see at a beach the 
lovemaking and pillow talk we see have an intimacy and sexy 
tenderness that can only be called healthy 
as their love affair intensifies steven matures as an artist 
and as a man hadley seems happy at last and yet there is an 
ominous note in all this thats not audible in the background 
music 
and speaking of music theres lots of luscious mozart chopin 
and tchaikovsky in the sound track thanks to mona golabek a 
worldclass pianist who coached the actors on keyboard technique 
and performed many of the solos 
kudos also to the tremendously talented james stacy a longtime 
character actor who plays the disabled father with a special fire 
and pain 
not every viewer will realize that there is no clever makeup 
effect or standin at work stacy actually is disabled his 
impairments may limit the roles he can play but not his range 
the strengths of matters of the heart are its actors they 
create people who are recognizable and human and their 
relationships begin evolve and end 
what weakens the movie is that cowriters linda bergman and 
martin tahses plot devices are shopworn youll say aha the 
old lost dog to reunite the lovers gag surely here well see a 
clever twist on the old old story 
you will wait in vain for such higher designs 
theres even one unforgivable scene in which the lovers frolic 
in the snow affectionately lobbing snowballs at each other it 
looks like a chewing gum commercial do you suppose the director 
said ok kids rollick 
matters of the heart is not sophisticated it doesnt 
advance the art of romance who cares its the day after 
christmas tuck the kids away put on your new bathrobe and bunny 
slippers and curl up with someone cuddly 
surely matters of the heart deserve some attention tonight 
 
elsewhere in television 
more drama in television news barbara eden and heather locklear 
star on new years day in the madeforcbs movie her wicked 
ways which is billed as a contemporary drama of 
behindthescenes power struggles in broadcast news 
miss eden plays a respected television network white house 
correspondent who is next in line for the allimportant network 
anchor chair miss locklear plays an ambitious reporter whose 
devious machinations threaten all that 
miss eden a clever comedian beloved for her work in i dream 
of jeannie is cast here in a fantasy without comedy miss 
locklear wellknown for her work on dynasty and tj 
hooker has her work cut out for her 
