winning the olympics alone would have given 
atlanta reason to crow this year but then the heavyweight 
championship and what about landing a super bowl and a spot on 
the most liveable list and now grits meets glitz jane 
fonda too 
this citys triumphs finally gave substance to its boosters old 
nickname in 1990 it was hotlanta indeed 
true the olympics fireworks burst over a city that would pass a 
curfew to save its children from drug dealers true the mayor had 
to challenge preliminary census figures indicating his city was 
losing people 
but even if the ticker tape snowed on a cooling economy and on 
troubles common to urban area atlanta celebrated as it hadnt 
since the curtain went up on gone with the wind half a century 
ago 
in september a few months after being picked as the site of pro 
footballs 1994 super bowl dark horse atlanta beat out athens 
