<TEXT>
at john brown shipyard on clydeside in scotland the great 
depression halted work for two years on hull no 534 idling more 
than 3500 workers but the queen mary the mostbeloved of all 
cunard ships finally made her maiden voyage on may 27 1936 
when the ship reporters came aboard from the pilot boat there 
was never a shortage of royalty real or hollywood on the 
cunarders emperor haile selassie of ethiopia the shah of iran and 
the sultan of jahore favored the queen mary as did the exiled 
edward viii and the duchess of windsor who traveled with 75 trunks 
in the hold and 70 pieces of luggage in their suite 
film queens from mary pickford to elizabeth taylor climbed up on 
the rail wreathed in a life preserver for the requisite 
