<TEXT>
the rows of honeycured hams waiting to be 
stacked aboard federal express jets gave a clear message to those 
in the know it was christmas time and time was running out 
when it gets late they go for things like hams packaged 
foods things you can order from a catalogue or a store thatll 
send them straight to us said dan copp a federal express 
spokesman and makeshift tour guide for the airlines sprawling 
cargo hub at memphis 
with the largest cargo airline in the world federal express 
stays busy year round but the basic organized madness of its 
memphis hub gets even brisker as the christmas deadline nears 
the holiday season starts making itself known in november when 
the package delivery company typically handles 15 million items 
worldwide this years oneday record was over 2 million on dec 
20 
the company guarantees overnight service anywhere in the united 
states but for the standard lastminute holiday shoppers friday 
was the deadline for prechristmas delivery 
federal express was founded in memphis on a hub system that 
brought all packages here from throughout the country before 
reshipment to their final destinations the system has been 
modified somewhat over the years but 65 percent of federal 
express packages still move through memphis the companys 
superhub 
it is aptly named 
with some 14 million square feet of covered space the total 
hub takes up 295 acres more than 5500 workers labor in the hub 
when its humming and 35 miles of conveyor belts carry thousands 
of packages through a stainless steel network of platforms stairs 
and observation towers 
hallways throughout the hub are dotted with closedcircuit tvs 
broadcasting a constant flow of information for workers from 
weather reports and package volumes to the latest employee stock 
options 
federal express has 94000 workers worldwide 
at the memphis hubs first level for separating the thousands of 
items from around the country hustling workers put packages on a 
conveyor belt and key their zip codes into a computer the computer 
times a packages movement along the belt and a mechanical arm 
swings out at the appropriate moment to move it from one belt to 
another depending on the code 
before long all items for california end up heading to one 
general area while those for say north carolina take another 
route the hub has 19 substations based on zip codes 
teams of workers at those various stations make finer 
destination distinctions once selected for a particular route an 
item is then packed with hundreds of others in enclosed shipping 
containers that link up to move through the hub like small trains 
led by tractors the trains then head outside to the jets 
</TEXT>
