the state bank warned foreign banks and financial 
institutions monday not to accept illegal payments in rubles from 
soviet banks and businesses 
the central bank said soviet enterprises recently have tried to 
make tens of billions of rubles worth of payments to foreign 
companies claiming they have the governments backing 
but soviet law forbids either individuals or businesses from 
exporting more than 30 rubles without special permission 
the ruble is not convertible and soviet businesses and joint 
ventures pay foreign bills either with hard currency through bank 
transfers or by barter arrangements 
there have been numerous reports recently by various sources 
about the emergence of payment documents in rubles payable 
checks bills letters of guarantee issued by soviet banks and 
enterprises for tens of billions of dollars the bank said in a 
statement carried by the tass news agency 
