sixmonth bills rose to 693 percent as the discount increased rose 
2 basis points to 662 percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 
698 percent as the discount gained 4 basis points to 655 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks was trading at 7 percent down from 7 percent late friday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds closed at 91 532 down lsqb point the average 
yield to maturity rose to 748 percent from 747 percent late 
friday 
