<TEXT>
the chicago mercantile exchange the chicago 
board of trade and reuters holdings plc on monday announced a 
tentative agreement on globex their proposed electronic futures 
and options trading system 
the parties said they reached agreement on a letter of intent 
that resolves all substantive issues toward the completion of a 
20year contract 
the letter of intent is subject to execution of a final 
agreement approval by the parties governing boards and 
ratification by the exchanges members according to a statement 
the longdelayed system is scheduled for testing in chicago new 
york and london around the end of the first quarter the parties 
said 
globex is envisioned as a worldwide computerized system for 
trading the financial futures and options products of various 
exchanges when their trading floors are closed reuters would 
supply the computer terminals and the technology 
the new york mercantile exchange the sydney futures exchange of 
australia and the french futures exchange known as matif have 
agreed to offer products for trading on globex alongside selected 
products from the merc and the board of trade 
the merc and londonbased reuters had announced plans for globex 
in september 1987 and originally hoped to have the system in 
operation by the spring of 1989 
the project was delayed by international regulatory hurdles and 
negotiations with the board of trade which agreed to join the 
project last may after abandoning an attempt to create a competing 
system 
