<TEXT>
stock prices declined moderately monday in listless christmas 
eve trading 
activity was sparse throughout the session which closed for the 
impending holiday at 2 pm est two hours earlier than usual 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials dropped 1237 points to 
262129 
bond prices were down amid hightened middle east war talk 
in london crude oil futures prices rose about 1 a barrel on the 
international petroleum exchange the new york mercantile exchange 
was closed for the holidays 
wheat and oat futures rose on the chicago board of trade while 
corn and soybean futures ended mostly lower in the shortened 
trading session 
